subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. Body slender. Ocellar setae absent or rather short and weak (compared to those of 

Euthycera

). Lunule clearly visible. Most species with 1 pair of scutellar setae. Hind femur of both males and females with distinct blunt ventral spines in apical 1/3 (indistinct or absent in 

Euthycera

). Wing in most species hyaline with reticulated pattern or with sparse pale spots.
